  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&quot;In December 2015, world leaders reached a historic climate agreement at COP21 in Paris, sending a clear signal to governments and businesses to accelerate their efforts to decarbonize their economies, supply chains, and business models. However, investment in low-carbon, climate-resilient activities is far short of the need to meet internationally agreed goals. Climate Policy Initiative, through financial analysis and convening, helps ensure that policymakers and decision makers have the knowledge and tools to spend more money, more wisely, to address climate change while achieving sustainable development goals.&quot;</narrative>
  </description>
